    <stitle>FRONT DRIVE AXLE WHEEL ENDS: ROCKWELL - DISASSEMBLY - BRAKE AND SPINDLE FROM STEERING KNUCKLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>BRAKE AND SPINDLE FROM STEERING KNUCKLE</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>Non-asbestos fibers in brake lining may be a cancer and lung disease hazard. Caution must be
                    exercised in handling and maintenance.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the air or hydraulic brake lines at the brake assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If used, remove the air brake chambers. Refer to GROUP 04-AIR BRAKES in the CTS-5000 Master
                Service Manual.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To disassemble the oil slinger and brake assembly from the spindle and steering knuckle,
                remove the attaching capscrews. Note: some brake models require that the shoe return springs be removed
                before the capscrews can be reached.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the spindle straight from the knuckle and drive shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200806">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200806" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg02/G0200806.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Removing Spindle Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The felt seal and retainer, if used, and the sleeve and thrust washer will remain inside the
                spindle. If necessary, disassemble these pieces with a screwdriver or sharp tool (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200807">Figure 7</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200807" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg02/G0200807.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Exploded View of Seal, Retainer, Sleeve and Thrust Washer</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SLEEVE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. THRUST WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. RETAINER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. FELT SEAL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
